 1942\u201345 | publisher = Random House | location =  | isbn = 1-4000-6413-9 | url = https://archive.org/details/survivingswordpr00maca }}\n* Lingen, Kerstin von, ed. ''War Crimes Trials in the Wake of Decolonization and Cold War in Asia, 1945-1956.'' (Palgrave Macmillan, Cham, 2016) [https://www.palgrave.com/gp/book/9783319827100 online]\n* {{Cite book | last = Minear | first = Richard H. | authorlink = Richard Minear | year = 1971 | title = Victor's Justice: The Tokyo War Crimes Trial | publisher = Princeton University Press | location = Princeton, NJ, USA}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Maga | first = Timothy P. | authorlink = | year = 2001 | title = Judgment at Tokyo: The Japanese War Crimes Trials | publisher = University Press of Kentucky | location = | isbn = 0-8131-2177-9}}\n* Neier, Aryeh. ''War Crimes: Brutality, Genocide, Terror and the Struggle for Justice,'' Times Books, Random House, New York, 1998.\n* {{Cite book | last = Piccigallo | first = Philip R. | authorlink = | year = 1979 | title = The Japanese on Trial: Allied War Crimes Operations in the East, 1945\u20131951 | publisher = University of Texas Press | location = Austin, Texas, USA}}\n* Rees, Laurence. ''Horror in the East'', published 2001 by the British Broadcasting Company\n* Seagrave, Sterling & Peggy. ''Gold warriors: America's secret recovery of Yamashita's gold, Verso Books, 2003. {{ISBN|1-85984-542-8}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Sherman | first = Christine | authorlink = | year = 2001 | title = War Crimes: International Military Tribunal | publisher = Turner Publishing Company | location = | isbn = 1-56311-728-2}}-Detailed account of the [[International Military Tribunal for the Far East]] proceedings in Tokyo\n* Trefalt, Beatrice . \"Japanese War Criminals in Indochina and the French Pursuit of Justice: Local and International Constraints.\" ''Journal of Contemporary History'' 49.4 (2014): 727-742.\n* {{Cite book | last = Tsurumi | first = Kazuko | authorlink =  | year = 1970 | title = Social change and the individual: Japan before and after defeat in World War II | publisher = Princeton University Press | location = Princeton, USA | isbn = 0-691-09347-4 | url = https://archive.org/details/socialchangeindi0000tsur }}\n* Williams, Peter. ''Unit 731: Japan's Secret Biological Warfare in World War II'', Free Press, 1989. {{ISBN|0-02-935301-7}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Wilson | first = Sandra|display-authors=etal | authorlink = | year = 2017 | title = Japanese War Criminals: The Politics of Justice After the Second World War | publisher = Columbia University Press | location = New York, USA | isbn = 9780231179225}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Yamamoto | first = Masahiro | authorlink = | year = 2000 | title = Nanking: Anatomy of an Atrocity | publisher = Praeger Publishers | location = | isbn = 0-275-96904-5}}- A rebuttal to Iris Chang's book on the Nanking massacre.\n{{refend}}\n\n===Audio/visual media===\n{{refbegin}}\n* Minoru Matsui (2001), [http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/east/04/07/japan.devils/index.html ''Japanese Devils''], documentary with interview of veteran soldiers from the Imperial Japanese Army (Japanese ''Devils shed light on a dark past'') CNN\n** [http://www.midnighteye.com/reviews/japdevil.shtml ''Japanese Devils''], Midnight Eye,\n* {{Cite video | people= The History Channel | date= 2000 | url= | title = Japanese War Crimes: Murder Under The Sun | medium = Video documentary (DVD & VHS) | location = | publisher= A & E Home Video}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Please alphabetize according to display title -->\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070609112646/http://home.pacbell.net/fbaldie/Battling_Bastards_of_Bataan.html Battling Bastards of Bataan]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080113004217/http://www.sjwar.org/ \"Biochemical Warfare \u2013 Unit 731\". Alliance for Preserving the Truth of Sino-Japanese War.] No date.\n* [http://www.warbirdforum.com/cannibal.htm \"Cannibalism\". Dan Ford, \"Japan at War, 1931\u20131945\"]